<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,601,1535,1561]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Family 
<taxonomicName authority="Grube, 1859" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1859" box="[247,601,1535,1561]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnocharidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Limnocharidae Grube, 1859</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1607,1742]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
At the larval stage, limnocharids are known to parasitize aquatic bugs (
<bibRefCitation author="Bottger, K." box="[960,1113,1608,1634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="109 - 152" refId="ref70915" refString="Bottger, K. (1972) Vergleichend biologisch-okologische Studien zum Entwicklungszyklus der Susswassermilben (Hydrachnellae, Acari). I. Der Entwicklungszyklus von Hydrachna globosa und Limnochares aquatica. Internationale Revue der gesamten Hydrobiologie, 57, 109 - 152. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / iroh. 19720570105" type="journal article" year="1972">Böttger 1972</bibRefCitation>
, B.P. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, B. P." box="[1179,1326,1607,1634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="2238 - 2243" refId="ref73121" refString="Smith, B. P. (1989 a) Impact of parasitism by larval Limnochares aquatica (Acari: Hydrachnidia; Limnocharidae) on juvenile Gerris comatus, Gerris alacris and Gerris nuenoi (Insecta: Hemiptera; Gerridae). Canadian Journal of Zoology, 67, 2238 - 2243. https: // doi. org / 10.1139 / z 89 - 316" type="journal article" year="1989">Smith 1989a</bibRefCitation>
), but also Odonata (
<bibRefCitation author="Petzold, F. &amp; Martin, P." box="[261,524,1643,1670]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="91 - 97" refId="ref72796" refString="Petzold, F. &amp; Martin, P. (2004) Limnochares aquatica als Parasit von Leucorrhinia albifrons (Hydrachnidia: Limnocharidae; Odonata: Libellulidae). Libellula, 23, 91 - 97." type="journal article" year="2004">Petzold &amp; Martin 2004</bibRefCitation>
) and aquatic beetles (B.P. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, B. P." box="[820,968,1643,1670]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="445 - 452" refId="ref73187" refString="Smith, B. P. (1989 b) A description of the larva of Rhyncholimnochares kittatinniana Habeeb (Hydrachnidia; Limnocharidae). Canadian Entomologist, 121, 445 - 452. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 121445 - 6" type="journal article" year="1989">Smith 1989b</bibRefCitation>
), while adults feed on insect larvae (
<bibRefCitation author="Bottger, K." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="85 - 91" refId="ref70879" refString="Bottger, K., (1970) Die Ernahrungsweise der Wassermilbe Limnochares aquatica (L.) (Hydrachnellae, Acari). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 33 (Supplement), 85 - 91." type="journal article" year="1970">Böttger 1970</bibRefCitation>
). Tuzovskij &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R." box="[426,603,1679,1706]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="127 - 145" refId="ref71559" refString="Gerecke, R. (2009) Revisional studies on Thoracophoracarus K. Viets, 1914 (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Arrenuridae). Zoosystema, 31, 127 - 145. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2009 n 1 a 7" type="journal article" year="2009">Gerecke (2009)</bibRefCitation>
give a survey on the diversity of this fauna in 
<collectingCountry box="[1141,1278,1679,1705]" name="Madagascar" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, reporting the presence of six species.
</paragraph>
